# IAM feature documentation

Before modifying **OIDC, SSO sessions, federation, WebAuthn, MFA, multi-tenant auth, or platform admin authorization**:

1. Read [docs/README.md](../../docs/README.md) (hub: routes, DB tables, Redis keys).
2. Read the relevant [docs/features/*.md](../../docs/features/) guide for the feature you are changing.

After behavior changes, update in the same PR:

- Matching [docs/features/*.md](../../docs/features/) and [docs/testing/*.md](../../docs/testing/) guide
- [documentation-standards.mdc](documentation-standards.mdc) doc map if paths or scope changed
- `make swagger-load` + commit spec files when `/api/v1` HTTP surface changed

**Authorization:** use [docs/features/AUTHORIZATION.md](../../docs/features/AUTHORIZATION.md) — platform admin (`users.is_platform_admin`) and tenant membership roles (`tenant_memberships.role`).

Skill: [skills/feature-knowledge/SKILL.md](../skills/feature-knowledge/SKILL.md)
